  "texts": [
    "In current neuromodulation devices, the design and material of the neural interface are crucial for their wider adoption and exploitability 32.",
    "An adequate neural interface should be able to create selective contact with different fascicles in the nerve bundles to restore the efferent and afferent neural pathways effectively.",
    "To achieve a selective electrical interface to the PNS, various types of microelectrodes have been developed and used over the last years 32, 196.",
    "The design usually depends on the respective application.",
    "Often, very small structures are required to meet the high demands on selectivity and to address very small regions of neural tissue, e.g."
  ]
}